import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['fertility']]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='fertility', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {data["fertility"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility across all countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.show()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.title('How has life expectancy changed over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='fertility', ascending=False).head(10)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='country', y='fertility', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.title('What are the top 10 countries with the highest fertility rates?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['fertility'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Fertility Rate: {:.2f}'.format(data['fertility'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='n_fertility', data=data, label='Normalized Fertility Rate')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='n_life_expect', data=data, label='Normalized Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('How does the normalized fertility rate compare to the normalized life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Normalized Value')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
